Spiderman

Biological webbing

Strength

Camouflage

Speed

Energy

Venom Blast

Hibernating Healing

Durability

Weaknesses:

Water

Ethyl Chloride

Story:

The American teenager Peter Parker, an orphaned boy living with his Aunt and Uncle, was bitten by a radioactive spider. As a result of the bite he gains superhuman speed, and strength and spider powers, such as clinging to surfaces and ceilings like a spider, and detecting danger with his precognition ability called spider senses. He develops web slinging devices both for fighting and for web swinging across the city. He originally used his powers for his own gain until his Uncle Ben was killed by a thief that Peter could not stop. He then vowed to use his powers for good to fight crime by becoming Spider-Man.

jackieharris123456789
item.content:encoded:
Superman

Strengths

Strength

Speed

Leaping

Durability

Mind Abilities

X-ray Vision

Power Transfer

Weaknesses

Kryptonite

Magic

Red Sun

High Voltage Electricity

Atomic Radiation

Inability to See through Lead

Mind Control

Life Threatening Viruses

Story

Kal-El was born on Krypton. As the planet was about to be destroyed his parents built a spacecraft, put him in it and sent him off. He landed in a rural part of earth. He was found and adopted and named Clark Kent. His parents discovered he had superpowers at a young age and taught him to use his powers for good. He keeps his powers hidden to protect his family and friends from criminals. In order to save humanity he created the alter ego Superman.
